text: Diandrya composita is a species of cestode parasites that is known from marmots (Marmota spp.) in North America. Described along with the genus Diandrya by J. G. Darrah in 1930, is known from all North American marmots except the woodchuck (M. monax). == References == Category:Cestoda Category:Parasites of rodents
title: Diandrya composita
